<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880209-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Meredith Names Burnett Chairman, Rehm President </HL><AUTHOR> Cynthia Crossen (WSJ Staff) </AUTHOR><SO> </SO><CO> MDP WNEWS </CO><TEXT>   Robert A. Burnett was named chairman of Meredith Corp., a diversified media company that publishes nine magazines, including its flagship, Better Homes andamp; Gardens.    Mr. Burnett, 60 years old, who had been president and chief executive officer, succeeds E.T. Meredith III, 55, who will continue as chairman of the executive committee. Mr. Meredith is the grandson of the founder of the Des Moines, Iowa-based company. Mr. Burnett will continue as chief executive.    Also, Jack Rehm was named president and chief operating officer, a position that hasn't existed for several years. Mr. Rehm, 55, who was previously executive vice president -- corporate services, was also named a director.    Meredith has a program in which managers are expected to identify potential successors for their positions. Although Mr. Burnett hasn't announced any retirement plans, Mr. Rehm's promotion makes him a leading candidate to eventually become chief executive.    Mr. Rehm will assume responsibility for the day-to-day operation of all of Meredith's magazine and book publishing, broadcasting, real estate and printing operations. Mr. Burnett will continue to be responsible for the overall management of the company and will directly oversee corporate staff functions. </TEXT></DOC>